metadata.name: Negative Space #170
metadata.description:
In this piece, special attention is paid to negative space, which is emphasized by simple / bold color palettes.

6 different styles
- Network
- Parachutes
- Flow
- Limbs
- Arcs
- Florals

9 different color palettes
- dark
- light
- yellow
- blue
- red
- green
- blue and yellow
- red and blue
- multi

Press any key to download a hi-res png.

p5.js script with a custom shader. Depending on the settings, it take some time to fully render / draw.

metadata.name: Mandaloids #34
metadata.description:
Note that these pieces render progressively via pathtracing in WebGL, so will take some time to converge to the final image.

Pan and zoom interactively to exlore detail. The camera focus adjusts automatically. Zoom the browser window (Ctrl key + "-") to render at higher resolution (and "P" to save the image).

metadata.name: mezcal #485
metadata.description:
a reflection/meditation on the idea that over time, we hold certain memories as perfect moments in time. they are not still like a photograph. they flow like a river, searching and branching out into the fractal of our existence.
over time they can become something completely different. but if the memory is all that's left. then what was ever true to begin with ?

--------------------------

press 's' to save png to device. artwork resolution regenerates according to window size.

to create a higher resolution image: zoom out as much as possible, then hit refresh.
tested with chrome.

metadata.name: Effet papillon #97
metadata.description:
The butterfly effect is a term in the natural sciences that refers to the property of some chaotic systems: a slight influence on the system can have large and unpredictable consequences, including in a completely different place.

Made with p5.js
